you can use a univeristy personal site for uploads and downloads:
enter the server:

$ ssh comserver

then go to ~/.public_html

and set your files for download, or create your own webpage index.html

also you can link the files to git repo on this page, using info from:

http://lisas.de/~adrian/?p=61

to sincronise the git folder with the hocschule public domain do:
$ rsync -avP -e "ssh" . asaramet@rzlx0900:~/.public_html/Downloads/foamRemoteDistro

the HE user page URL is:
http://www2.hs-esslingen.de/~asaramet/

# copy the bwGRiD web page to HE/~asaramet:
rsync -avh ./bwGRiD asaramet@rzlx0900.hs-esslingen.de:~/.public_html

# update the bwGRiD web page from local pc to HE/~asaramet:
rsync -uavh ./bwGRiD asaramet@rzlx0900.hs-esslingen.de:~/.public_html
